      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/20/179",
      "text": [
        " «يُكْرَهُ ذَلِكَ حَتَّى يَتَوَضَّأَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.179 - Ubaydullah ibn Ali Al-Halabi said:\n‘Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) was asked whether it is appropriate for a man to sleep while in a state of janabah (ritual impurity from sexual discharge).’\nImam (as) replied: 'It is disliked (makruh) to do so without first performing wudu (ablution).'"
        ]
      }
    },
